when The Cars broke up,

518
00:21:52,920 --> 00:21:54,529
but look at me now.

519
00:21:55,488 --> 00:21:57,184
What happened last year?

520
00:21:57,228 --> 00:21:59,621
[Grady] Ah, just more
stupid kids.

521
00:21:59,666 --> 00:22:01,362
♪

522
00:22:01,407 --> 00:22:06,062
I felt like Colin was--
was my--my dad, my papa,

523
00:22:06,107 --> 00:22:08,326
my brother, my lover,
all those things.

524
00:22:08,370 --> 00:22:10,197
You know, when you're
standing there in the mosh pit,

525
00:22:10,241 --> 00:22:13,069
and you just know that
he's talking right to you--

526
00:22:13,114 --> 00:22:14,897
I mean, it's almost like
he looked right at me.

527
00:22:14,942 --> 00:22:17,683
And I felt like maybe I was
just another face in the crowd,

528
00:22:17,727 --> 00:22:19,859
but he loved everyone, you know?

529
00:22:19,903 --> 00:22:22,514
He, like, singled out everyone
in his own way.

530
00:22:22,558 --> 00:22:24,994
He's everywhere.
He's everything.

531
00:22:25,039 --> 00:22:26,387
He's--he's in the wind.

532
00:22:26,432 --> 00:22:27,693
He's very powerful.

533
00:22:27,737 --> 00:22:29,695
And that is so fucking cool.

534
00:22:29,739 --> 00:22:31,697
And whether he's alive or dead
doesn't matter

535
00:22:31,741 --> 00:22:33,525
because he's everywhere.

536
00:22:33,569 --> 00:22:35,788
[Colin] ♪ Love

537
00:22:35,832 --> 00:22:39,008
♪ What if there was no love?

538
00:22:39,053 --> 00:22:41,663
Must get wicked boring.

539
00:22:41,708 --> 00:22:42,838
What?

540
00:22:42,883 --> 00:22:44,274
Being dead.

541
00:22:45,102 --> 00:22:46,712
I oughta know.

542
00:22:47,583 --> 00:22:50,411
I was operated on for a hernia
when I was a kid.

543
00:22:51,282 --> 00:22:53,893
They put me under
for, like, four hours.

544
00:22:53,937 --> 00:22:55,851
I got no memory of it.

545
00:22:55,896 --> 00:22:58,985
Just black.
No dreams.

546
00:22:59,029 --> 00:23:01,509
And then I woke up in the hall.

547
00:23:01,554 --> 00:23:03,816
That's what death is.

548
00:23:03,860 --> 00:23:05,731
A big nothing.

549
00:23:06,689 --> 00:23:08,211
I've been there.

550
00:23:08,256 --> 00:23:10,910
This is all you get right here.

551
00:23:10,954 --> 00:23:12,694
You sure you don't want a beer?

552
00:23:12,739 --> 00:23:15,088
What about all those people
who have near-death experiences?

553
00:23:15,132 --> 00:23:16,785
They see, like, a light.

554
00:23:16,830 --> 00:23:19,745
Ah, the key word there
is "near-death."

555
00:23:19,789 --> 00:23:21,573
What do you think?
There's someplace you go to

556
00:23:21,617 --> 00:23:24,010
where free mineral water
comes out of the ground

557
00:23:24,054 --> 00:23:26,142
and everyone's a poet?

558
00:23:26,187 --> 00:23:28,362
God created this planet
and then said, "See ya."

559
00:23:28,407 --> 00:23:29,668
We better hope
He doesn't come back,

560
00:23:29,712 --> 00:23:31,191
or He might be pissed.

561
00:23:31,235 --> 00:23:34,237
So you believe in God
but not an afterlife?

562
00:23:34,282 --> 00:23:36,196
What's wrong with that?

563
00:23:36,240 --> 00:23:39,591
