♪ Come on, baby,
Don't you come too soon ♪

767
00:32:09,928 --> 00:32:12,233
♪ Sing along
'Cause you know the tune ♪

768
00:32:12,278 --> 00:32:14,714
♪ I won't stop moving
Till I touch the moon ♪

769
00:32:14,758 --> 00:32:17,847
♪ I said shoot,
Shoot for the moon ♪

770
00:32:17,892 --> 00:32:20,589
♪ Come on, baby,
Don't you come too soon ♪

771
00:32:20,634 --> 00:32:23,331
♪ Sing along
'Cause you know the tune ♪

772
00:32:23,376 --> 00:32:27,640
Oooooooooh.

773
00:32:27,684 --> 00:32:30,860
Ooooooh.

774
00:32:30,905 --> 00:32:34,690
[laughs evilly]

775
00:32:34,735 --> 00:32:37,302
[growling]

776
00:32:39,522 --> 00:32:40,740
Shit.

777
00:32:40,784 --> 00:32:41,959
[both chuckle]

778
00:32:42,003 --> 00:32:43,830
Did I scare you?

779
00:32:45,093 --> 00:32:47,921
Did I scare you?
[chuckles]

780
00:32:47,966 --> 00:32:49,836
When?

781
00:32:49,880 --> 00:32:52,578
With the flashlight
under my face.

782
00:32:53,536 --> 00:32:55,102
I guess not.

783
00:32:58,063 --> 00:32:59,846
Are you a policeman?

784
00:32:59,890 --> 00:33:02,631
Um, oh, no.

785
00:33:03,459 --> 00:33:06,984
I was hired to guard, um...

786
00:33:08,987 --> 00:33:10,639
this place.

787
00:33:13,078 --> 00:33:16,819
You--you're not really
supposed to be here.

788
00:33:16,864 --> 00:33:18,952
Because of last year?

789
00:33:18,997 --> 00:33:20,214
What?

790
00:33:21,303 --> 00:33:22,869
Last year.

791
00:33:23,523 --> 00:33:26,090
That's why you're here,
isn't it?

792
00:33:26,134 --> 00:33:27,917
Oh, um...

793
00:33:29,224 --> 00:33:30,920
I don't know.
[chuckles]

794
00:33:32,358 --> 00:33:34,228
I was here.

795
00:33:34,273 --> 00:33:36,143
When?

796
00:33:36,188 --> 00:33:37,927
-Last year.
-Oh.

797
00:33:37,972 --> 00:33:39,233
Yeah.

798
00:33:39,278 --> 00:33:41,279
♪

799
00:33:41,323 --> 00:33:43,411
Right where you're standing.

800
00:33:43,456 --> 00:33:46,675
♪

801
00:33:46,720 --> 00:33:48,634
[crickets chirping]

802
00:33:49,679 --> 00:33:51,463
[car approaching]

803
00:33:56,295 --> 00:33:57,512
[engine turns off]

804
00:33:57,557 --> 00:34:00,602
♪

805
00:34:03,258 --> 00:34:04,606
[car door shuts]

806
00:34:04,651 --> 00:34:07,087
-Do you want to come in?
-Yeah.

807
00:34:07,132 --> 00:34:08,741
[Grady] Well, well, well,
hello, Moira.

808
00:34:08,785 --> 00:34:10,047
Grady, what are you doing here?

809
00:34:10,091 --> 00:34:12,092
[Grady] Yeah, yeah.

810
00:34:12,137 --> 00:34:14,747
-Oh, yeah.
-What's up, Grady?

811
00:34:14,791 --> 00:34:17,402
-Tony, come inside.
-Go ahead, babycakes.

812
00:34:17,446 --> 00:34:19,099
I'll be right in.

813
00:34:20,449 --> 00:34:22,450
How's the baby shark, Tony?

814
00:34:23,409 --> 00:34:25,801
-He's dead, man.
-Oh.

815
00:34:25,846 --> 00:34:27,803
-Can I have him?
-What?

816
00:34:27,848 --> 00:34:29,936
Well, since you got my woman,
maybe you could--

817
00:34:29,980 --> 00:34:31,546
I told you he's dead, man.

818
00:34:31,591 --> 00:34:33,853
Yeah, well,
what'd you do with him?

819
00:34:33,897 --> 00:34:36,247
You didn't eat him, did ya?

820
00:34:36,291 --> 00:34:38,945
Why don't you go now,
rent-a-cop?

821
00:34:38,989 --> 00:34:41,208
Too big to flush down
the toilet, I bet, yeah.

822
00:34:41,253 --> 00:34:43,297
Did ya bury him in the backyard?

823
00:34:43,342 --> 00:34:45,995
Why don't you go back
to the mall, mall cop?

824
00:34:46,040 --> 00:34:48,041
Can I have the tank?

825
00:34:48,086 --> 00:34:51,175
The little, baby, teeny tank

826
00:34:51,219 --> 00:34:53,699
for the little dead baby shark?

827
00:34:53,743 --> 00:34:57,529
Why don't you get outta here
now, rent-a-mall-cop?

828
00:34:57,573 --> 00:35:02,055
Yeah, well, I'd like to use it
to raise my own deadbaby shark.

829
00:35:02,100 --> 00:35:04,362
♪

830
00:35:04,406 --> 00:35:07,147
There was an ad posted
in the record store.

831
00:35:07,192 --> 00:35:10,281
It was for a thing
called toy piano lessons.

832
00:35:10,325 --> 00:35:13,240
Now, if you just bought
Colin Fitz's albums,

833
00:35:13,285 --> 00:35:15,895
that wouldn't mean
anything to you, 'kay?

834
00:35:15,939 --> 00:35:19,768
But if you listen to all
his import singles, like I did,

835
00:35:19,813 --> 00:35:22,380
then you would know
that "Toy Piano Lessons"

836
00:35:22,424 --> 00:35:26,253
is one of the songs
off a Swedish bootleg CD.

837
00:35:26,298 --> 00:35:29,256
He's very big in Sweden.

838
00:35:29,301 --> 00:35:32,607
So, there was a number
on the flyer, so I called it.

839
00:35:32,652 --> 00:35:35,480
And a guy said there'd be
a meeting in the park.

840
00:35:35,524 --> 00:35:37,090
So I went.

841
00:35:37,135 --> 00:35:38,657
There was a bunch
of other people there,

842
00:35:38,701 --> 00:35:43,314
but nobody talked
except this one guy.

843
00:35:43,358 --> 00:35:46,882
He was dressed
just like Colin Fitz.

844
00:35:46,927 --> 00:35:49,494
-He wore his hair just like him.
-[Colin singing indistinctly]

845
00:35:49,538 --> 00:35:53,715
He mentioned Colin Fitz
in just about every sentence.

846
00:35:53,760 --> 00:35:56,631
He was singing all
of Colin Fitz's songs.

847
00:35:56,676 --> 00:35:59,721
He sounded exactly like him.

848
00:36:00,723 --> 00:36:02,550
It was weird.

849
00:36:02,595 --> 00:36:05,162
He said he was possessed
by Colin Fitz,

850
00:36:05,206 --> 00:36:10,297
that Colin Fitz
was singing through him.

851
00:36:10,342 --> 00:36:12,125
I don't know what I believed,

852
00:36:12,170 --> 00:36:14,171
but everyone else
seemed to believe him,

853
00:36:14,215 --> 00:36:16,651
so I went to
a couple more meetings.

854
00:36:17,914 --> 00:36:21,221
They got more and more...

855
00:36:22,397 --> 00:36:23,963
believable.

856
00:36:24,007 --> 00:36:25,704
♪

857
00:36:25,748 --> 00:36:28,446
He started talking
about the anniversary.

858
00:36:28,490 --> 00:36:30,317
It was coming up,

859
00:36:30,362 --> 00:36:33,625
and how we should all
join him at the cemetery.

860
00:36:33,669 --> 00:36:35,801
We all sat around the grave,

861
00:36:35,845 --> 00:36:38,630
and we listened to him
play some songs.

862
00:36:38,674 --> 00:36:40,806
It was really beautiful.

863
00:36:40,850 --> 00:36:44,853
Then he told us
to bow our heads

864
00:36:44,898 --> 00:36:47,900
and think of
a positive memory of Colin.

865
00:36:48,597 --> 00:36:49,945
Like...

866
00:36:51,252 --> 00:36:53,471
the first time
we heard his voice.

867
00:36:53,515 --> 00:36:56,082
♪

868
00:36:56,126 --> 00:37:00,347
He was handing out paper cups
filled with grape juice.

869
00:37:00,392 --> 00:37:04,221
Everybody got one,
but nobody drank right away.

870
00:37:04,265 --> 00:37:06,048
We all looked to the leader.

871
00:37:06,093 --> 00:37:08,094
♪

872
00:37:08,138 --> 00:37:12,229
Then he said a prayer,
and he took a sip from his cup.

873
00:37:14,057 --> 00:37:16,363
He smiled at all of us

874
00:37:17,409 --> 00:37:20,411
and laid down
right by the grave.

875
00:37:21,456 --> 00:37:24,284
Then everyone took a sip
from their cup

876
00:37:24,329 --> 00:37:27,069
and laid down
on top of the grave.

877
00:37:28,507 --> 00:37:30,464
I watched them.

878
00:37:32,250 --> 00:37:34,903
I looked at my cup.

879
00:37:34,948 --> 00:37:37,123
♪

880
00:37:37,167 --> 00:37:39,256
I took a sip.

881
00:37:40,997 --> 00:37:44,652
I tried to swallow,
but I couldn't.

882
00:37:44,697 --> 00:37:51,833
♪

883
00:37:51,878 --> 00:37:57,012
I went home and stayed
in my room for two days.

884
00:37:57,057 --> 00:37:59,972
I heard about the others
on the radio.

885
00:38:00,016 --> 00:38:03,454
♪

886
00:38:03,498 --> 00:38:06,239
No one ever came looking for me.

887
00:38:07,981 --> 00:38:10,896
No one knew I was there.

888
00:38:10,940 --> 00:38:13,942
Everyone else was dead, so...

889
00:38:14,727 --> 00:38:17,250
[crying]

890
00:38:21,168 --> 00:38:23,691
Sometimes, when the wind blows,

891
00:38:23,736 --> 00:38:26,346
he sings,
and he tells me things.

892
00:38:26,391 --> 00:38:27,652
[interviewer]
What does he tell you?

893
00:38:27,696 --> 00:38:30,785
He tells me sometimes,
um, that--

894
00:38:30,830 --> 00:38:32,831
things--like, important
things, like, real things

895
00:38:32,875 --> 00:38:35,660
like I'm out of, like, bread.

896
00:38:35,704 --> 00:38:38,402
He'll say, "You need to go
to the grocery store."

897
00:38:39,621 --> 00:38:41,883
And I go.

898
00:38:41,928 --> 00:38:44,625
[Tony, Grady grunting]

899
00:38:55,245 --> 00:38:57,899
Tony, go inside and dry off.
Now!

900
00:39:06,518 --> 00:39:08,170
Dirty.

901
00:39:09,042 --> 00:39:11,173
Just go, Grady, please.

902
00:39:12,567 --> 00:39:14,089
So this means
I don't have to get you

903
00:39:14,134 --> 00:39:16,222
a birthday present
this year, right?

904
00:39:16,266 --> 00:39:17,571
Only if you want to.

905
00:39:17,616 --> 00:39:19,399
Well, I wanted
to get you something. I--

906
00:39:19,444 --> 00:39:21,445
I had something all picked out.

907
00:39:21,489 --> 00:39:23,229
Maybe I'll get it
for someone else.

908
00:39:23,273 --> 00:39:24,317
I hope you do.

909
00:39:24,362 --> 00:39:26,537
Maybe I'll get one for myself.

910
00:39:26,581 --> 00:39:27,842
Good.
You should.

911
00:39:27,887 --> 00:39:29,888
You should
take care of yourself.

912
00:39:29,932 --> 00:39:32,543
[Grady] I can take care
of myself.

913
00:39:32,587 --> 00:39:34,327
-I hope so.
-You don't think I can?

914
00:39:34,372 --> 00:39:36,285
You can.
You can if you try.

915
00:39:36,330 --> 00:39:38,244
You know, maybe if you would
do something productive

916
00:39:38,288 --> 00:39:40,072
instead of those
stupid animal posters.

917
00:39:40,116 --> 00:39:42,466
-You like those.
-The first one, yeah.

918
00:39:42,510 --> 00:39:44,381
You know, now, it's--
it's just wrong.

919
00:39:44,425 --> 00:39:46,731
-You're leading people on.
-Come on.

920
00:39:46,775 --> 00:39:49,647
Did you put the one about
the pony up at the laundromat?

921
00:39:49,691 --> 00:39:51,083
Yeah.

922
00:39:51,127 --> 00:39:53,390
See, even I'm starting
to believe them.

923
00:39:54,827 --> 00:39:56,654
You broke my heart.

924
00:39:59,353 --> 00:40:01,310
Ah, man.

925
00:40:01,355 --> 00:40:03,835
-Moira?
-What?

926
00:40:05,185 --> 00:40:06,620
If you and Tony
don't work out--

927
00:40:06,665 --> 00:40:08,361
-I will.
-You will what?

928
00:40:08,406 --> 00:40:09,884
I will what what?

929
00:40:09,929 --> 00:40:11,495
If you and Tony
don't work out, you will?

930
00:40:11,539 --> 00:40:13,279
-I don't know.
-What were you gonna say?

931
00:40:13,323 --> 00:40:15,760
-Nothing.
-Well, I was gonna say,

932
00:40:15,804 --> 00:40:18,023
if you and Tony don't work out,
I won't be at all surprised.

933
00:40:18,067 --> 00:40:19,764
-Oh, just go.
-And if you need someone

934
00:40:19,808 --> 00:40:22,201
to cheat on him with,
give me a call.

935
00:40:22,245 --> 00:40:23,898
That way, you don't have to
interview a bunch of guys

936
00:40:23,943 --> 00:40:25,639
since I've had the job before.

937
00:40:25,684 --> 00:40:28,250
♪

938
00:40:28,295 --> 00:40:31,993
[Colin]
♪ She's a pretty alligator

939
00:40:32,038 --> 00:40:35,170
♪ I know I won't escape her

940
00:40:35,215 --> 00:40:38,130
♪ A pretty alligator

941
00:40:38,174 --> 00:40:39,827
♪ She gonna eat me alive

942
00:40:39,872 --> 00:40:42,439
♪ I know I won't
survi-ai-ai-ai-ai-oh! ♪

943
00:40:42,483 --> 00:40:45,224
♪

944
00:40:45,268 --> 00:40:47,922
♪ Pretty alligator

945
00:40:47,967 --> 00:40:49,620
♪ She gonna eat me alive

946
00:40:49,664 --> 00:40:52,927
♪ I know I won't
survi-ai-ai-ai-ai-oh! ♪

947
00:40:54,234 --> 00:40:56,365
♪ Oww!

948
00:40:56,410 --> 00:40:59,499
♪

949
00:40:59,544 --> 00:41:01,675
♪ I'm gonna die, die,
Die, die ♪

950
00:41:01,720 --> 00:41:03,372
[tires squealing]

951
00:41:03,417 --> 00:41:05,810
♪ Die-ai-ai-ai-ai-ai-ai-oww!

952
00:41:05,854 --> 00:41:08,813
♪ I'm gonna die

953
00:41:08,857 --> 00:41:11,206
[Colin fan] You never thought
of killing yourself?

954
00:41:12,165 --> 00:41:14,122
Come on.

955
00:41:14,167 --> 00:41:16,821
You're a security guard.

956
00:41:16,865 --> 00:41:18,213
Hey.

957
00:41:18,998 --> 00:41:20,607
This is not my career, you know?

958
00:41:20,652 --> 00:41:21,869
I mean, I do other things.

959
00:41:21,914 --> 00:41:24,089
Like what?

960
00:41:24,133 --> 00:41:26,744
Uh, I write poetry.

961
00:41:26,788 --> 00:41:28,920
♪

962
00:41:28,964 --> 00:41:30,225
Go ahead.
Make fun of that.

963
00:41:30,270 --> 00:41:31,618
No.
Can I hear one?

964
00:41:31,663 --> 00:41:32,924
No.

965
00:41:36,798 --> 00:41:39,365
You're not from here, are you?

966
00:41:39,409 --> 00:41:40,540
No.

967
00:41:40,585 --> 00:41:42,237
Where you from?

968
00:41:42,935 --> 00:41:45,023
I move around a lot.

969
00:41:45,764 --> 00:41:48,853
Where were you a year ago?

970
00:41:50,508 --> 00:41:51,725
A year ago today?

971
00:41:51,770 --> 00:41:54,293
-Mm-hmm.
-Um...

972
00:41:56,209 --> 00:41:57,252
Texas.

973
00:41:57,297 --> 00:41:59,385
No.
I don't know.

974
00:41:59,429 --> 00:42:00,865
[chuckles]

975
00:42:00,909 --> 00:42:03,171
What's in Texas?

976
00:42:03,216 --> 00:42:04,869
Less people.

977
00:42:06,001 --> 00:42:07,349
Less questions.

978
00:42:07,394 --> 00:42:09,395
Am I asking too many questions?

979
00:42:09,439 --> 00:42:10,918
No.

980
00:42:11,529 --> 00:42:13,181
I'm just kidding.

981
00:42:13,922 --> 00:42:18,535
Did you ever know anybody
that killed themselves?

982
00:42:18,579 --> 00:42:21,625
I went out with a girl
who had problems.

983
00:42:21,669 --> 00:42:23,627
What kind of problems?

984
00:42:23,671 --> 00:42:25,542
You know.

985
00:42:25,586 --> 00:42:28,240
No.
What?

986
00:42:28,284 --> 00:42:33,724
Well, I had to keep, like,
scissors away from her.

987
00:42:33,768 --> 00:42:35,377
Or else what?

988
00:42:35,422 --> 00:42:36,988
She'd hurt herself?

989
00:42:38,294 --> 00:42:39,599
Or me.

990
00:42:39,644 --> 00:42:41,558
She stabbed you?

991
00:42:43,212 --> 00:42:45,387
Not so you'd notice.

992
00:42:45,432 --> 00:42:46,998
Where did she stab you?

993
00:42:47,042 --> 00:42:48,869
[wind rustling]

994
00:42:51,786 --> 00:42:53,439
In Texas.

995
00:42:57,618 --> 00:42:59,358
So what happened to her?

996
00:43:02,144 --> 00:43:03,797
I'm sorry.

997
00:43:09,021 --> 00:43:10,587
Can I hear a poem?

998
00:43:10,631 --> 00:43:13,633
♪

999
00:43:17,464 --> 00:43:19,813
The light under your door

1000
00:43:19,858 --> 00:43:25,384
made you alive once again there.

1001
00:43:25,428 --> 00:43:27,821
♪

1002
00:43:27,866 --> 00:43:29,127
Although you're not there.

1003
00:43:29,171 --> 00:43:31,651
♪ I was a child

1004
00:43:31,696 --> 00:43:33,218
You're miles gone.

1005
00:43:33,262 --> 00:43:36,961
♪ You were a child to me

1006
00:43:37,005 --> 00:43:39,616
But you were ever present.

1007
00:43:40,313 --> 00:43:42,270
♪ For it taught me

1008
00:43:42,315 --> 00:43:44,055
Just a knock away.

1009
00:43:44,099 --> 00:43:46,100
♪ I never knew

1010
00:43:47,755 --> 00:43:51,366
-What's that about?
-♪ God, I miss you

1011
00:43:51,411 --> 00:43:57,155
♪

1012
00:43:57,199 --> 00:43:58,330
Nothing.

1013
00:43:58,374 --> 00:44:00,985
♪ Oh, I miss you

1014
00:44:01,029 --> 00:44:02,682
You shouldn't be here.

1015
00:44:02,727 --> 00:44:05,032
Can I stay a little longer?

1016
00:44:05,077 --> 00:44:06,425
Please?
I need to be here.

1017
00:44:06,469 --> 00:44:08,340
Please, don't make me go.

1018
00:44:08,384 --> 00:44:13,127
♪ Toy piano lessons

1019
00:44:13,172 --> 00:44:14,694
♪

1020
00:44:14,739 --> 00:44:16,348
I guess, you know,
I was pretty pissed off

1021
00:44:16,392 --> 00:44:17,741
when he kicked me
down the stairs,

1022
00:44:17,785 --> 00:44:19,568
but after,
when he came into the hospital

1023
00:44:19,613 --> 00:44:22,441
and he dressed up like a clown
and shit, that was pretty funny.

1024
00:44:22,485 --> 00:44:23,921
[interviewer] Is that how
you got the neck brace?

1025
00:44:23,965 --> 00:44:25,487
Yeah, like six years ago.

1026
00:44:25,532 --> 00:44:27,489
We got in a fight.

1027
00:44:27,534 --> 00:44:29,317
I mean,
I kind of half-fell, kinda.

1028
00:44:29,362 --> 00:44:31,232
He shoved, but, you know,
